(max,+) algebra

Possibly (min,+) too.
Two operations taking over the role of addition and multiplication: \oplus and \otimes
Define the new operations as \boxed{
x\oplus y \equiv \max(x,y)
}

\boxed{
x\otimes y \equiv x+y}




Indeed, there is no typo here, the addition is replaced by \otimes and not \oplus.
And why the other name ‚Äútropical‚Äù? Reportedly just to honor a matematician who contributed to the field and lived in Brazil.

